  "text": "-Different assumptions made for variables without data: the uncertainties are especially high for countries without a strong statistical record and sectors and gases, which need several assumptions for the calculation of emissions. Power sector CO 2 emissions have relatively low uncertainty if a good record for power plant technology, the fuels used, and their electricity production exists. Agricultural emissions, on the other hand, have a high uncertainty as the emissions are based on natural processes, which depend on locally and seasonally fluctuating variables like soil moisture (see, e.g., [CITATION_1] . See also Fig. 7 .",
